      "description": "This E46 M3 represents the pinnacle of naturally aspirated Bavarian engineering. Under the hood lies the S54B32 power plant, featuring six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing, delivering linear power delivery up to an 8,000 RPM redline. The chassis remains structurally flawless with documented subframe reinforcement already completed. Power is managed via a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable differential lock. Suspension geometry is dialed to factory specifications, utilizing fresh bushings and Bilstein dampers to ensure optimal turn-in response. This example is collector-grade, showing zero signs of mechanical wear or cosmetic degradation.",
